<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12018i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12018i">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12018i"> 18(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Maire disposses Merovingien / kings, shows them to / people on shield, / tonsures them</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Car les M&eacute;rovingiens n&apos;&eacute;taient plus, &agrave; cette &eacute;poque, que des fant&ocirc;mes de rois, des mannequins entre les mains des maires du palais. Mais le respect superstitieux pour cette famille, &eacute;puis&eacute;e par ses d&eacute;bauches et ses crimes, subsistait dans le peuple. La Neustrie et l&apos;Austrasie se disputaient avec acharnement ces simulacres de royaut&eacute;. Le maire usurpateur les faisait &eacute;lever sur le bouclier aux acclamations des Franks, puis les enfermait dans une ville et r&eacute;gnait &agrave; leur place. Presque tous finissaient ou assassin&eacute;s, ou honteusement <font color="green">[158]</font> tonsur&eacute;s, au fond d&apos;un convent. <br><font color="green">[Because the Merovingians were no longer, at this time, but ghosts of kings, mannequins in the hands of the palace mayors. But the superstitious respect for that family, exhausted by their crimes and debauchery, remained among the people. Neustria and Austrasia fought with zeal over the semblances of royalty. The usurpating mayor had them lifted onto the shield to the acclamation of the Franks, then locked up in the city and reigned in their place. Almost all of them ended either killed or shamefully tonsured in the bottom of a convent.]</font> <small> &Eacute;douard Schur&eacute;, <a name="ESLL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ESLL"><cite title="source">Les Grandes L&eacute;gendes de France</cite></a> (1892) 158</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
